1904 St. Louis World's Fair, early American plays about the Philippines, Filipino patrons in U.S. taxi dance halls to the phenomenon of Filipino/a actors in Miss Saigon. Using this varied archive, Puro Arte turns to performance as an object of study and as a way of understanding complex historical processes of racialization in relation to empire and colonialism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jun 2020) 0aEthnicityxPolitical aspectsxPhilippines. 0aEthnicityxPolitical aspectszPhilippines. 0aFilipino AmericansxEthnic identity. 0aImperialismxSocial aspectsxPhilippines. 0aImperialismxSocial aspectszPhilippines. 0aNationalismxSocial aspectsxPhilippines. 0aNationalismxSocial aspectszPhilippines. 0aPerforming artsxPolitical aspectsxPhilippines. 0aPerforming artsxPolitical aspectsxUnited States. 0aPerforming artsxPolitical aspectszPhilippines. 0aPerforming artsxPolitical aspectszUnited States. 0aPopular culturexPolitical aspectsxPhilippines. 0aPopular culturexPolitical aspectsxUnited States. 0aPopular culturexPolitical aspectszPhilippines. 0aPopular culturexPolitical aspectszUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNYUP Backlist 2000-2013z978311070644440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814708132423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780814708132.jpg  a978-3-11-070644-4  NYUP Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK